premise_source_doc_sentence: Macbeth  (  -LSB- məkˈbɛθ -RSB- full title The Tragedy of Macbeth  )  is a tragedy by William Shakespeare ; it is thought to have been first performed in 1606 .

William Shakespeare  (  -LSB- ˈʃeɪkspɪə -RSB- 26 April 1564  (  baptised  )  -- 23 April 1616  )  was an English : poet , : playwright , and actor , widely regarded as the greatest writer in the English language and the world 's pre-eminent dramatist .

The Complete Works of William Shakespeare  (  Abridged  )   (  also known as The Compleat Wrks of Wllm Shkspr  (  Abridged  )   )  is a play written by Adam Long , Daniel Singer , and Jess Winfield that parodies the plays of William Shakespeare with all of them being performed  (  in comically shortened or merged form  )  by only three actors .
Lady Macbeth is a character from William Shakespeare 's play Macbeth .
Lord Banquo -LSB- ˈbæŋkwoʊ -RSB- , the Thane of Lochaber , is a character in William Shakespeare 's 1606 play Macbeth .

The three actors first introduce themselves to the audience , the first actor  (  Reed Martin  )  reminding the audience not to record the show , the second  (  Austin Tichenor  )  giving a speech about how unappreciated William Shakespeare is and the third  (  Adam Long  )  giving a biography of Shakespeare mixed up with a biography of Adolf Hitler .
